NIGERIAN born singer Adaorah is set to release her new single, Rock My Borry. According to Adaorah Music Management, the single was produced by Andre Vibez, one of Nigeria’s finest and creative producer. Speaking on the new song, Adaorah says the track takes listeners through a journey of love and sacrifice while seducing the listener with Oja, the elegant Igbo flute.   Patience Ozokwo: It’s hard raising children with manners     Why I divorced Korra Obidi, by ex-husband     Olu Jacobs’ daughter-in-law makes u-turn, says Soji…   In a short chat with the singer, she said it has always been her dream to take the Nigerian music scene by storm, which is doing well worldwide. “As an Igbo girl, my tradition is important to me and that is why even when I’m not fully living in Nigeria, I want everything about my music to reflect our culture. I love our sound—the rhythm, the storytelling, our vibrant flow, and how our music makes you feel. I am a big fan of artists like Davido, Wizkid, 2baba, Burna boy, Flavor and Tiwa Savage and look forward to working with them someday soon”. The single, Adaorah says, will be released on April 16, 2022.